                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_gærtam" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>gærtam</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>gærtan</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>взятка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bribe</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>подкуп</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>graft</q></tr></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>gærtamxor</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>взяточник („взяткоед“)</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>bribe-taker (“bribe-eater”)</q></tr></sense></re><exampleGrp><example><quote>ræsuǧd Bela gærtam wydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>красавица Бэла послужила взяткой</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>beautiful Bela served as a bribe</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>188–189</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>ræsuǧd Bela gærtam wydi</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>красавица Бэла послужила взяткой</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>beautiful Bela served as a bribe</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>188–189</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">За пределами осетинского слово прослеживается в грузинском, русском и финских (пермских) языках: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>krtami</w> <gloss><q>дар</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>подношение</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>взятка</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(стар. и обл.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(obsolete and regional) </note><w>ко́ртома</w> <gloss><q>аренда</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/> <gloss><q>наем</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/> <gloss><q>откуп</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/> <gloss><q>условная плата за наем чего-нибудь</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>кортомить</w> <gloss><q>брать в наем, на откуп</q></gloss></mentioned>, (%i%bотдавать, брать в кортому%b%i), <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/> <w>körtöm, körtəm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/> <w>kertəm</w> <gloss><q>аренда</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="udm"><w/> <gloss><q>наем</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Случайно созвучие с <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>χάρτωμα</w></mentioned>. На пермской почве слово может этимологизироваться на основе глагола %ikört%i || %ikert-%i ‘связывать’. В этом случае придется допустить, что в русский и кавказские языки слово вошло из финских. Однако осетинское %igærtam%i по значению и огласовке примыкает к груз. %ikrtami%i и должно считаться усвоенным оттуда.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Munkácsi._Alan."/><biblScope>326</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><biblScope>Blüten 189</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">103 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">103 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Ахвледиани"/><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Outside Ossetic, the word can be traced in the Georgian, Russian and Finnish (Permic) languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/> <w>krtami</w> <gloss><q>donation</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>offering</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/> <gloss><q>bribe</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/> <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">(стар. и обл.) </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en">(obsolete and regional) </note><w>ко́ртома</w> <gloss><q>rent</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/> <gloss><q>hire</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/> <gloss><q>lease</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w/> <gloss><q>conditional payment for hiring something</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>кортомить</w> <gloss><q>hire out</q></gloss></mentioned>, (%i%bотдавать, брать в кортому%b%i), <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/> <w>körtöm, körtəm</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="udm"><lang/> <w>kertəm</w> <gloss><q>rent</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="udm"><w/> <gloss><q>hire</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The similarity with <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/> <w>χάρτωμα</w></mentioned> is accidental. If this word comes from Permic languages, than it might be etymologized on the basis of the verb %ikört%i || %ikert-%i ‘tie’. In this case one have to assume that this word entered Russian and Caucasian languages via Finnic ones. However, Ossetic %igærtam%i is close to Georgian %ikrtami%i in the meaning and the sound form and it should be considered acquired from it.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Munkácsi._Alan."/><biblScope>326</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl><biblScope>Blüten 189</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Sköld._Oss."/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">103 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">103 ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Ахвледиани"/><biblScope>43</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><note type="internal">нужен особый посткоммент к циту</note></entry></body></text></TEI>